    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Processing_PreProcessingStatusReport",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to generate a report on the status of account processing for a specified billing period. It retrieves data from two main sources: active accounts from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.Account",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table and manual billing data from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ManualBill.AccountManualBillingHeader",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. The procedure provides a summary of active accounts and their billing statuses, including counts of received, vouchered, transferred, and unvouchered items."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple table joins, conditional aggregations, and uses a transaction isolation level of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". While the logic is straightforward, the complexity arises from the need to accurately aggregate and join data from different sources."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
